HEADWORD: Empawn
<hw>Em*pawn"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>em-</ets> + <ets>pawn</ets>. Cf. <er>Impawn</er>.]</ety> <def>To
put in pawn; to pledge; to impawn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To sell, <qex>empawn</qex>, and alienate the estates.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Empeach</ent>⟦br⟧
